============================================================
SUMMARY CHANGELOG FROM THE PREVIOUS CHAT
============================================================

Major desktop/Codex changes completed:

1. Desktop/mobile map popup parity
- Deprecated the old desktop `#app-panel` behavior.
- Kept the old app panel code in the repo for now, but it is no longer the active interaction path.
- Desktop hex clicks now use the same Leaflet popup/preview-card style as mobile.
- Popup uses the existing map preview/card flow.
- Details from popup opens the relevant Codex detail page.
- This was done for consistency and to simplify map interaction logic.

2. Codex glyph/icon cleanup
- Kept Maps, Hexes, and NPCs mostly as-is.
- POIs use `◎`.
- Regions use `✥`.
- Search uses the mirrored/overridden `⌕`.
- Lore uses `▤`.
- The glyph overrides were committed into the main files.
- Future possibility: replace glyphs with SVG icons, but not now.

3. Left page pseudo-manuscript / pseudo-language system
- Added decorative pseudo-language text to the left Codex page.
- It generates from syllable fragments and occasional marks.
- Syllables can combine into word-like clusters, sometimes with apostrophes/hyphens.
- Random seed generation happens per Codex page render.
- It should not regenerate on every search input keystroke.
- Search page should generate once when results page opens and again when navigating away, not per character.
- Mark fragments are pulled less often than syllable fragments.
- Text was made more visible, multi-column, and less slanted.
- Safe-area placement was adjusted leftward to stay in the ink-safe left-page area.

4. Google Drive image resolver / asset system
- Added Codex asset resolver support.
- Image fields can contain:
  - Google Drive file IDs
  - Google Drive share links
  - normal relative paths / URLs
- Supported/future-friendly fields include:
  - `Image_File_ID`
  - `Image`
  - `Image_URL`
  - `Region_Image_File_ID`
  - `POI_Image_File_ID`
  - `POI_Group_Image_File_ID`
  - `NPC_Image_File_ID`
  - `Portrait_File_ID`
  - `Map_Image_File_ID`
- Google Drive images resolve to:
  `https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=FILE_ID&sz=w1600`
- Map/image click targets use the thumbnail URL, not the Drive shell page.
- Blank image fields use normal placeholders.
- Broken/unavailable images show missing indicators:
  - `Image unavailable`
  - `Map unavailable`
  - `Map not recorded`

5. Detail/record images
- NPC images use `contain` so full portraits show.
- Map images use `contain`.
- POI/POI group/region scenic images use `cover`.
- Region index tiles remain more scenic/tile-like.
- Resolved images are rendered as real image layers above placeholders.
- For contain images, JS calculates rendered image dimensions so the edge fade follows the actual image bounds rather than the entire container.
- The separate outlines/borders around images were removed/suppressed; edge transparency itself is the only intended “outline.”
- A cleanup stylesheet was added to suppress slot backgrounds once real images load.

6. Map tile visual polish
- Map tiles were made to more closely match region tiles.
- Added stronger bottom transparency fade.
- Added region-tile-style title glow/stroke.
- Map tile text/lower title treatment was adjusted.

7. Image modal
